<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Stafford Heights.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Stafford Heights?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Stafford Heights values are driven by access to Kedron Brook parklands, proximity to Westfield Chermside, block size and condition. Families seeking more land than Chermside or Kedron can offer find Stafford Heights delivers comparable amenity at a stronger price-per-square-metre. Homes with Kedron Brook outlook or large rear gardens consistently outperform the suburb average.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Stafford Heights?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented Stafford Heights homes correctly priced against Stafford and Kedron comparables typically sell within 28 to 45 days. The suburb attracts a motivated buyer pool from families who have been tracking the northern corridor for several months and arrive with clear priorities.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Stafford Heights?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Stafford Heights offers a practical north Brisbane lifestyle with good arterial access, walking distance to Kedron Brook and Westfield Chermside within easy reach. The suburb suits families who want space and convenience without the density of suburbs closer to the CBD. Local parks and sporting facilities give the suburb a community feel.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Stafford Heights a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Stafford Heights presents good value relative to Kedron and Chermside, which are tighter on land and more expensive. Buyer demand from families upgrading within the northern corridor has remained solid, and the suburb's access to major retail and arterial roads makes it an attractive entry point into north Brisbane at a reasonable price level.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

